38 /* Peripheral: AAR */
39 /* Description: Accelerated Address Resolver. */
40 
41 /* Register: AAR_INTENSET */
42 /* Description: Interrupt enable set register. */
43 
44 /* Bit 2 : Enable interrupt on NOTRESOLVED event. */
45 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
46 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
47 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
48 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
49 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Set (1UL)
51 /* Bit 1 : Enable interrupt on RESOLVED event. */
52 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
53 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos)
54 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
55 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
56 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Set (1UL)
58 /* Bit 0 : Enable interrupt on END event. */
59 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
60 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos)
61 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
62 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
63 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
65 /* Register: AAR_INTENCLR */
66 /* Description: Interrupt enable clear register. */
67 
68 /* Bit 2 : Disable interrupt on NOTRESOLVED event. */
69 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
70 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
71 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
72 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
73 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
75 /* Bit 1 : Disable interrupt on RESOLVED event. */
76 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
77 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos)
78 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
79 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
80 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
82 /* Bit 0 : Disable interrupt on ENDKSGEN event. */
83 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
84 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
85 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
86 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
87 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
89 /* Register: AAR_STATUS */
90 /* Description: Resolution status. */
91 
92 /* Bits 3..0 : The IRK used last time an address was resolved. */
93 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos (0UL)
94 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Msk (0xFUL << AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos)
96 /* Register: AAR_ENABLE */
97 /* Description: Enable AAR. */
98 
99 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable AAR. */
100 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
101 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
102 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0x00UL)
103 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (0x03UL)
105 /* Register: AAR_NIRK */
106 /* Description: Number of Identity root Keys in the IRK data structure. */
107 
108 /* Bits 4..0 : Number of Identity root Keys in the IRK data structure. */
109 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos (0UL)
110 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Msk (0x1FUL << AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos)
112 /* Register: AAR_POWER */
113 /* Description: Peripheral power control. */
114 
115 /* Bit 0 : Peripheral power control. */
116 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Pos (0UL)
117 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_POWER_POWER_Pos)
118 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Disabled (0UL)
119 #define AAR_POWER_POWER_Enabled (1UL)
122 /* Peripheral: ADC */
123 /* Description: Analog to digital converter. */
124 
125 /* Register: ADC_INTENSET */
126 /* Description: Interrupt enable set register. */
127 
128 /* Bit 0 : Enable interrupt on END event. */
129 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
130 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_INTENSET_END_Pos)
131 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
132 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
133 #define ADC_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
135 /* Register: ADC_INTENCLR */
136 /* Description: Interrupt enable clear register. */
137 
138 /* Bit 0 : Disable interrupt on END event. */
139 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
140 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
141 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
142 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
143 #define ADC_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
145 /* Register: ADC_BUSY */
146 /* Description: ADC busy register. */
147 
148 /* Bit 0 : ADC busy register. */
149 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Pos (0UL)
150 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Pos)
151 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Ready (0UL)
152 #define ADC_BUSY_BUSY_Busy (1UL)
154 /* Register: ADC_ENABLE */
155 /* Description: ADC enable. */
156 
157 /* Bits 1..0 : ADC enable. */
158 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
159 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
160 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0x00UL)
161 #define ADC_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (0x01UL)
163 /* Register: ADC_CONFIG */
164 /* Description: ADC configuration register. */
165 
166 /* Bits 17..16 : ADC external reference pin selection. */
167 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_Pos (16UL)
168 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_Pos)
169 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_None (0UL)
170 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_AnalogReference0 (1UL)
171 #define ADC_CONFIG_EXTREFSEL_AnalogReference1 (2UL)
173 /* Bits 15..8 : ADC analog pin selection. */
174 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Pos (8UL)
175 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Msk (0xFFUL << ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Pos)
176 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_Disabled (0UL)
177 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput0 (1UL)
178 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput1 (2UL)
179 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput2 (4UL)
180 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput3 (8UL)
181 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput4 (16UL)
182 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput5 (32UL)
183 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput6 (64UL)
184 #define ADC_CONFIG_PSEL_AnalogInput7 (128UL)
186 /* Bits 6..5 : ADC reference selection. */
187 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_Pos (5UL)
188 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_Pos)
189 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_VBG (0x00UL)
190 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_External (0x01UL)
191 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_SupplyOneHalfPrescaling (0x02UL)
192 #define ADC_CONFIG_REFSEL_SupplyOneThirdPrescaling (0x03UL)
194 /* Bits 4..2 : ADC input selection. */
195 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_Pos (2UL)
196 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_Msk (0x7UL << ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_Pos)
197 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_AnalogInputNoPrescaling (0x00UL)
198 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_AnalogInputTwoThirdsPrescaling (0x01UL)
199 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_AnalogInputOneThirdPrescaling (0x02UL)
200 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_SupplyTwoThirdsPrescaling (0x05UL)
201 #define ADC_CONFIG_INPSEL_SupplyOneThirdPrescaling (0x06UL)
203 /* Bits 1..0 : ADC resolution. */
204 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_Pos (0UL)
205 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_Msk (0x3UL << ADC_CONFIG_RES_Pos)
206 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_8bit (0x00UL)
207 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_9bit (0x01UL)
208 #define ADC_CONFIG_RES_10bit (0x02UL)
210 /* Register: ADC_RESULT */
211 /* Description: Result of ADC conversion. */
212 
213 /* Bits 9..0 : Result of ADC conversion. */
214 #define ADC_RESULT_RESULT_Pos (0UL)
215 #define ADC_RESULT_RESULT_Msk (0x3FFUL << ADC_RESULT_RESULT_Pos)
217 /* Register: ADC_POWER */
218 /* Description: Peripheral power control. */
219 
220 /* Bit 0 : Peripheral power control. */
221 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Pos (0UL)
222 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Msk (0x1UL << ADC_POWER_POWER_Pos)
223 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Disabled (0UL)
224 #define ADC_POWER_POWER_Enabled (1UL)
227 /* Peripheral: CCM */
228 /* Description: AES CCM Mode Encryption. */
229

231 /* Description: Shortcuts for the CCM. */
232 
233 /* Bit 0 : Shortcut between ENDKSGEN event and CRYPT task. */
234 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Pos (0UL)
235 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Pos)
236 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
237 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
239 /* Register: CCM_INTENSET */
240 /* Description: Interrupt enable set register. */
241 
242 /* Bit 2 : Enable interrupt on ERROR event. */
243 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Pos (2UL)
244 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Pos)
245 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Disabled (0UL)
246 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Enabled (1UL)
247 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Set (1UL)
249 /* Bit 1 : Enable interrupt on ENDCRYPT event. */
250 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Pos (1UL)
251 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
252 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
253 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
254 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Set (1UL)
256 /* Bit 0 : Enable interrupt on ENDKSGEN event. */
257 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
258 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
259 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Disabled (0UL)
260 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Enabled (1UL)
261 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Set (1UL)
263 /* Register: CCM_INTENCLR */
264 /* Description: Interrupt enable clear register. */
265 
266 /* Bit 2 : Disable interrupt on ERROR event. */
267 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Pos (2UL)
268 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Pos)
269 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Disabled (0UL)
270 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Enabled (1UL)
271 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Clear (1UL)
273 /* Bit 1 : Disable interrupt on ENDCRYPT event. */
274 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Pos (1UL)
275 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
276 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
277 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
278 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Clear (1UL)
280 /* Bit 0 : Disable interrupt on ENDKSGEN event. */
281 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
282 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
283 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Disabled (0UL)

285 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Clear (1UL)
287 /* Register: CCM_MICSTATUS */
288 /* Description: CCM RX MIC check result. */
289 
290 /* Bit 0 : Result of the MIC check performed during the previous CCM RX STARTCRYPT */

292 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Pos)

340 #define CLOCK_INTENSET_DONE_Disabled (0UL)

404 #define CLOCK_HFCLKSTAT_STATE_NotRunning (0UL)

454 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_SRC_RC (0UL)

456 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_SRC_Synth (2UL)
458 /* Register: CLOCK_CTIV */
459 /* Description: Calibration timer interval. */
460

465 /* Register: CLOCK_XTALFREQ */
466 /* Description: Crystal frequency. */
467 
468 /* Bits 7..0 : External Xtal frequency selection. */
469 #define CLOCK_XTALFREQ_XTALFREQ_Pos (0UL)
470 #define CLOCK_XTALFREQ_XTALFREQ_Msk (0xFFUL << CLOCK_XTALFREQ_XTALFREQ_Pos)
471 #define CLOCK_XTALFREQ_XTALFREQ_32MHz (0x00UL)
472 #define CLOCK_XTALFREQ_XTALFREQ_16MHz (0xFFUL)
475 /* Peripheral: ECB */
476 /* Description: AES ECB Mode Encryption. */
477 
478 /* Register: ECB_INTENSET */
479 /* Description: Interrupt enable set register. */
480
